definitions.definition: ( chiefly transitive ) To force sexual intercourse or other sexual activity upon (someone) without their consent . [from 16th c.]
( transitive , intransitive ) To seize by force . (Now often with sexual overtones.) [from late 14th c.]
( transitive ) To carry (someone, especially a woman) off against their will, especially for sex; to abduct . [from 15th c.]
( transitive ) To plunder , to destroy or despoil . [from 17th c.]
( slang , sometimes offensive ) To subject (another person) to a painful or unfair experience.

subdefinitions.definition: To overpower , destroy (someone); to trounce . [from 20th c.]
examples: My experienced opponent will rape me at chess.

subdefinitions.definition: To exploit an advantage, often involving money, where the other person has little choice but to submit.
examples: Have you seen the prices in that store lately? I got raped for $20 just buying a sandwich.

definitions.definition: To make haste ; to hasten or hurry .

main_definition: ( obsolete , intransitive or reflexive ) To make haste ; to hasten or hurry . [14th–16th c.]
